public class Solution {
    public boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
        if (n <= 0) {
            return false;
        }
        double log = Math.log(n) / Math.log(3);
        return log % 1 == 0;
    }
}
```

This solution uses the property of logarithms that `log(a^b) = b * log(a)`. So, `log(n) / log(3)` will give us the power to which 3 should be raised to get `n`. If the result is an integer, then `n` is a power of 3.

